// MongoDB Start From Here
Model the following movie system as a Graph database.
Consider a information about of movie and actors. One movie can have
more than one actor
1. Identify the labels and relationships, along with their properties, and
draw a high-level Graph model.
2. Create nodes and relationships, along with their properties, and
visualize your actual Graph model.

CREATE
(a1:Actor {name:'Shahrukh Khan', age:58}),
(a2:Actor {name:'Deepika Padukone', age:38}),
(a3:Actor {name:'Salman Khan', age:59}),

(m1:Movie {title:'Pathaan', year:2023, business:1050, awards:5}),
(m2:Movie {title:'Jawan', year:2023, business:1200, awards:7}),
(m3:Movie {title:'Kick', year:2014, business:400, awards:2}),

(a1)-[:ACTED_IN]->(m1),
(a1)-[:ACTED_IN]->(m2),
(a2)-[:ACTED_IN]->(m1),
(a2)-[:ACTED_IN]->(m2),
(a3)-[:ACTED_IN]->(m3);

3. Answer the Queries:

a. Find movie which made highest business.
MATCH (m:Movie)
RETURN m.title, m.business
ORDER BY m.business DESC
LIMIT 1;

b. Display details of movie along with actors.
MATCH (a:Actor)-[:ACTED_IN]->(m:Movie)
RETURN m.title AS Movie, collect(a.name) AS Actors;

c. List all the movie of “Shahrukh Khan”.
MATCH (a:Actor {name:'Shahrukh Khan'})-[:ACTED_IN]->(m:Movie)
RETURN m.title;

d. Display all movie having more than 2 awards received
MATCH (m:Movie)
WHERE m.awards > 2
RETURN m.title, m.awards;
